{"version":3,"timestamp":"2026-02-13T22:39:59.356Z","sessions":{"0162b24561eb38cb":{"agent":"claude","model":"claude-opus-4-6","prompts":[{"id":221,"timestamp":"2026-02-13T22:27:21.350Z","content":"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Break circular reference in `fcache.rs`\n\n## Context\n\n`FileCache` doesn't compile because of a chicken-and-egg initialization problem:\n\n1. `FileCache<K>` contains `lru_tracker: LruEvictionTracker<K>`\n2. `LruEvictionTracker::spawn()` requires a `Deleter<K>` impl\n3. `LruEntryDeleter<K>` implements `Deleter<K>` but needs `Arc<FileCache<K>>`\n4. At construction time (line 201), `FileCache` isn't built yet, so we can't pass `Arc<FileCache<K>>`\n\nSecondary issue: `K` is missing the `Sync` bound on the `FileCache` impl block.\n\n## Approach: Extract shared inner state\n\nExtract the fields that `LruEntryDeleter` needs into a separate `FileCacheShared<K>` struct. Both `FileCache` and `LruEntryDeleter` hold `Arc<FileCacheShared<K>>`. No cycle, no `Weak`, no runtime checks, no API change.\n\n**Why this over `Arc::new_cyclic`/`Weak`:** The deleter doesn't need the full `FileCache` — just the map, root path, and size counter. Extracting shared state is zero-overhead, keeps `new()` returning `Self` (no API break), and avoids runtime `Weak::upgrade()` checks on every deletion.\n\n## Changes — `lib/cache/fcache.rs`\n\n### 1. Create `FileCacheShared<K>`\n\nNew struct holding the state that both `FileCache` and `LruEntryDeleter` need:\n\n```rust\nstruct FileCacheShared<K: Eq + Hash> {\n    root_path: PathBuf,\n    map: scc::HashMap<K, CacheMapEntry>,\n    size_bytes: AtomicUsize,\n}\n```\n\nMove `path_for` and `delete_entry_from_disk_sync` to an `impl` block on this struct.\n\n### 2. Update `FileCache<K>`\n\n```rust\npub struct FileCache<K: Eq + Hash> {\n    shared: Arc<FileCacheShared<K>>,\n    file_generator: AtomicUsize,\n    max_size_bytes: usize,\n    lru_tracker: LruEvictionTracker<K>,\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Update `LruEntryDeleter<K>`\n\n```rust\nstruct LruEntryDeleter<K: Eq + Hash> {\n    shared: Arc<FileCacheShared<K>>,\n}\n```\n\n`new()` takes `Arc<FileCacheShared<K>>` instead of `Arc<FileCache<K>>`.\n\n### 4. Fix `FileCache::new()` construction\n\n```rust\nlet shared = Arc::new(FileCacheShared {\n    root_path: pbuf,\n    map: scc::HashMap::new(),\n    size_bytes: AtomicUsize::new(0),\n});\n\nOk(Self {\n    shared: Arc::clone(&shared),\n    file_generator: AtomicUsize::new(0),\n    max_size_bytes,\n    lru_tracker: LruEvictionTracker::spawn(\n        LruEntryDeleter::new(shared),\n        Self::LRU_EVICTION_MAX_BATCH_SIZE,\n    ),\n})\n```\n\n### 5. Update all `self.map` / `self.root_path` / `self.size_bytes` references\n\nReplace with `self.shared.map`, `self.shared.root_path`, `self.shared.size_bytes` throughout the impl blocks for `FileCache`, `AsyncReadableCache`, and `AsyncWritableCache`.\n\n`delete_entry_from_disk_async` stays on `FileCache` but calls `self.shared.path_for(...)` and `self.shared.size_bytes`.\n\n### 6. Add `Sync` bound\n\nChange the impl block (line 122) from:\n```rust\nimpl<K: Eq + Hash + Send + Copy + 'static> FileCache<K>\n```\nto:\n```rust\nimpl<K: Eq + Hash + Send + Sync + Copy + 'static> FileCache<K>\n```\n\nAlso add `Sync` to the `AsyncReadableCache` and `AsyncWritableCache` impl blocks.\n\n## Files modified\n\n- `lib/cache/fcache.rs` — all changes are in this single file\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\ncargo fmt --all && cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings && cargo test --quiet\n```\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/marko/.claude/projects/-Users-marko-work-gitfs/c4e4b2e0-4b7d-42fd-a5e0-f93dcde9a5ed.jsonl","tools":{"read":1},"duration":32},{"id":222,"timestamp":"2026-02-13T22:27:53.408Z","content":"Base directory for this skill: /Users/marko/.claude/plugins/cache/superpowers-marketplace/superpowers/4.1.1/skills/executing-plans\n\n# Executing Plans\n\n## Overview\n\nLoad plan, review critically, execute tasks in batches, report for review between batches.\n\n**Core principle:** Batch execution with checkpoints for architect review.\n\n**Announce at start:** \"I'm using the executing-plans skill to implement this plan.\"\n\n## The Process\n\n### Step 1: Load and Review Plan\n1. Read plan file\n2. Review critically - identify any questions or concerns about the plan\n3. If concerns: Raise them with your human partner before starting\n4. If no concerns: Create TodoWrite and proceed\n\n### Step 2: Execute Batch\n**Default: First 3 tasks**\n\nFor each task:\n1. Mark as in_progress\n2. Follow each step exactly (plan has bite-sized steps)\n3. Run verifications as specified\n4. Mark as completed\n\n### Step 3: Report\nWhen batch complete:\n- Show what was implemented\n- Show verification output\n- Say: \"Ready for feedback.\"\n\n### Step 4: Continue\nBased on feedback:\n- Apply changes if needed\n- Execute next batch\n- Repeat until complete\n\n### Step 5: Complete Development\n\nAfter all tasks complete and verified:\n- Announce: \"I'm using the finishing-a-development-branch skill to complete this work.\"\n- **REQUIRED SUB-SKILL:** Use superpowers:finishing-a-development-branch\n- Follow that skill to verify tests, present options, execute choice\n\n## When to Stop and Ask for Help\n\n**STOP executing immediately when:**\n- Hit a blocker mid-batch (missing dependency, test fails, instruction unclear)\n- Plan has critical gaps preventing starting\n- You don't understand an instruction\n- Verification fails repeatedly\n\n**Ask for clarification rather than guessing.**\n\n## When to Revisit Earlier Steps\n\n**Return to Review (Step 1) when:**\n- Partner updates the plan based on your feedback\n- Fundamental approach needs rethinking\n\n**Don't force through blockers** - stop and ask.\n\n## Remember\n- Review plan critically first\n- Follow plan steps exactly\n- Don't skip verifications\n- Reference skills when plan says to\n- Between batches: just report and wait\n- Stop when blocked, don't guess\n","tools":{"edit":31,"read":7},"duration":619},{"id":223,"timestamp":"2026-02-13T22:38:12.480Z","content":"move this into the shared structure\n    /// Given an entry, remove it from the disk and update the size of the cache accordingly.\n    ///\n    /// Gracefully handles the case where the file doesn't exist, which can happen if the file was\n    /// deleted after we read the file ID from the map, but before we tried to delete\n    /// the file.\n    async fn delete_entry_from_disk_async(&self, entry: &CacheMapEntry) -> std::io::Result<()> {\n        match tokio::fs::remove_file(self.shared.path_for(entry.fid)).await {\n            Ok(()) => {\n                self.shared\n                    .size_bytes\n                    .fetch_sub(entry.size_bytes, std::sync::atomic::Ordering::Relaxed);\n                Ok(())\n            }\n            // Note that there's a race condition between the deleter and the mutator in\n            // AsyncWritableCache. Either one of these operations atomically grabs the file ID (so\n            // accessing the file ID is safe), but then they race to delete the file.\n            //\n            // Consequently, it's quite possible that the file is already deleted by the time we\n            // try to delete it, and that's already fine with us, so we just treat that case as a\n            // successful deletion.\n            Err(e) if e.kind() == std::io::ErrorKind::NotFound => Ok(()),\n            Err(e) => Err(e),\n        }\n    }\n","tools":{"edit":4},"duration":62},{"id":224,"timestamp":"2026-02-13T22:39:14.527Z","content":"this is verbose\n        if self\n            .shared\n            .size_bytes\n            .load(std::sync::atomic::Ordering::Relaxed)\n\n\ncreate a new helper method in shared","tools":{"read":2,"edit":2},"duration":10}],"startedAt":"2026-02-13T22:27:21.350Z"}},"files":{"lib/cache/fcache.rs":[{